IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: International Relief Teams is a non-profit international relief and development organization
IRS990.MissionDesc: International Relief Teams is a non-profit international relief and development organization dedicated to alleviating human suffering by providing critical assistance to victims of disaster, profound poverty and neglect worldwide
IRS990.Desc: BUILDING HEALTHY COMMUNITIES: (1) NIGER AND THE DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF THE CONGO - PROVIDED MORE THAN $46 MILLION IN URGENTLY NEEDED MEDICINES(ENOUGH TO TREAT MORE THAN 250,000 PEOPLE) TO CLINICS AND HOSPITALS SERVING THE POOR; 2) GUATEMALA- IRT DISTRIBUTED FOOD SUPPLEMENTS MONTHLY TO NEARLY 13,000 VERY YOUNG CHILDREN (6 MONTHS - 2 YEARS OLD) SUFFERING FROM MALNUTRITION; 3) SAN DIEGO, CA- IRT PROVIDED WEEKEND FOOD BACKPACKS TO 104 FOOD INSECURE LOW-INCOME FAMILIES THROUGH ITS "FEEDING SAN DIEGO'S KIDS" PROGRAM;(4) MEXICO-IRT SUPPORTED THE MONTHLY FOOD AND EDUCATION NEEDS FOR MORE THAN 40 ABANDONED CHILDREN AT KIDS KINGDOM ORPHANAGE IN BAJA,CA;(S) MEXICO -IRT SENT 15 VOLUNTEERS TO BUILD A HOME FOR A LOWINCOME FAMILY LIVING IN AN IMPOVERISHED SETTLEMENT COMMUNITY IN TIJUANA.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: (1)CALIFORNIA (COVID-19 PANDEMIC) -IRT PROVIDED NEARLY 512,000 MEALS ($888,636) TO FAMILIES IMPACTED BY THE PANDEMIC;(2) UKRAINE (REFUGEE CRISIS) -IRT PROVIDED OVER $720,000 IN FOOD, SUPPLIES, HEALTH SERVICES, WATER AND SANITATION TO INTERNATIONALLY DISPLACED PEOPLE AND REFUGEES AFFLICTED BY THE RUSSIAN INVASION OF UKRAINE;(3) HAITI (EARTHQUAKE)-IRT PROVIDED $450,000 IN TARPS AND CONSTRUCTION SUPPLIES TO FAMILIES AFFECTED BY THE EARTHQUAKE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: (4)LOUISIANA (HURRICANE IDA) -IRT PROVIDED $259,431 IN MRE'S, TARPS, SOLAR LANTERNS, CHARGERS FOR HURRICANE VICTIMS;(5) INDIA (COVID-19 PANDEMIC) -IRT PROVIDED NEARLY $62,000 IN PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT FOR MEDICAL STAFF IN H0SPITALS;(6) MALAWI (TROPICAL STORM ANA) -IRT PROVIDED $50,000 IN CASH VOUCHERS TO FAMILIES AFFECTED BY THE STORM;(7) CALIFORNIA (CALIFORNIA FIRES)-IRT PROVIDED OVER $50,000 TO SEND CONSTRUCTION CREWS TO ASSIST IN THE REBUILDING OF HOMES OF FAMILIES AFFECTED BY THE FIRES;(8) PHILIPPINES (TYPHOON RAI) -IRT PROVIDED $48,250 IN SOLAR LAMPS AND CHARGERS TO FAMILIES AFFECTED BY THE TYPHOON.
